<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,650,1012]" box="[197,1436,762,788]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,320,762,788]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks:</emphasis>
Detailed descriptions of this species are given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Strack, H. L." box="[905,1064,762,788]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref23788" refString="Strack, H. L. (1993) The Polyplacophora of the Red Sea. Journal of the Malacological Society of Australia, 14, 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="1993">Strack (1993)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Anseeuw, B. &amp; Terryn, Y." box="[1120,1433,762,788]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref20618" refString="Anseeuw, B. &amp; Terryn, Y. (2004) Intertidal chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) from the coast of Jordan, Red Sea, with the description of a new species of Parachiton Thiele, 1909. Bollettino Malacologico, suppl. 5 (2003), 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="2004">Anseeuw &amp; Terryn (2004)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,650,1012]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">The investigated material comprises of an intermediate valve only, but the characteristic sculpture, formed by large, well separated granules, covering the entire tegmentum surface, is sufficient to identify the species.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,650,1012]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thiele" authorityYear="1909" box="[197,410,874,899]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Lucilina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="perligera">
<emphasis box="[197,410,874,899]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Lucilina perligera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be a rather rare species, and only a few living specimens are known (
<bibRefCitation author="Anseeuw, B. &amp; Terryn, Y." pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref20618" refString="Anseeuw, B. &amp; Terryn, Y. (2004) Intertidal chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) from the coast of Jordan, Red Sea, with the description of a new species of Parachiton Thiele, 1909. Bollettino Malacologico, suppl. 5 (2003), 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="2004">Anseeuw &amp; Terryn 2004</bibRefCitation>
). It was considered endemic to the Red Sea, so this new record considerably extends the distribution of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,1327,986,1012]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="distribution">
